Show HN: American Apocalypse (Novel) (2004)
text:
I wrote this novel in 2004.

The government declares a pandemic and rounds up dissenters into concentration camps. A rock band steps up to save the world.

After I wrote this and put it on my website, I had a huge number of hits from .gov and .mil sites that mapped to Virginia and a ton of hits from IPs in Iraq. About a week after, I came home and my neighbor told me the police were going through my trash cans. A couple days later, they shined spotlights through my window while I was in my place watching a movie with friends. A few days after that, my apartment was broken into and they left my shotgun, my cash and gold lying out, and took my laptop. The police came and decided it wasn't a normal burglary. My girlfriend and I moved to a motel, never slept there again, and fled the country the next week. We stayed out for 10 years.

It's not the greatest book but it's kind of ahead of its time in certain ways.

What would you do if you could read out any SaaS application? [OSS]
text:
Hey everyone,

imagine you could read out data of any SaaS application, what would it be? I’d like to understand use-cases you might have.

Here are some examples to get you going:

* Downloading invoices from Asana, Notion etc. * Get a list of projects from Asana as CSV * Get a list of users with their permission in Jira as CSV ...

What use-case for which application(s) would be interesting for you and why? Thank you.
